race.comment: BELLA CORAZON (10) bounced off her good first-up third, with a fast finishing win over 1300m at Rosehill. Looks to have more to offer and can overcome the awkward gate. Go close. VIRGIL'S GIFT (12) sharp filly going nicely through her grades. Started hard in the market again at start three when a dominant on-pace winner over 1400m at Randwick Kensington with the 58.5kg. Will slide across from the wide gate and not too sure where her ceiling is. FLYING THINKER (2) talented mare who dictated the speed with the 58kg when a narrow fourth at her second run back behind BELLA CORAZON. Likely improver with genuine prospects. ALABAMA FOX (11) raced without luck in Group company last time in and returns from a let-up after two runs back. Since fitted with a 799m tick-over trial placing and Zac Lloyd sticks. Capable of taking this out. MAID OF MOOLAH (7) has gone to a new level this prep and will push forward from the inside gate and prove hard to get past.
